# Sanity TypeGen: Query Result Types First

TypeGen generates two categories of types in `sanity.types.ts`. Always prefer category 2.

## Category 1 — Schema document types (avoid as props/utilities)
`FaqItem`, `Faq`, `SiteSettings`, `NavLink`, `Hero`, etc.
These represent the raw Sanity document shape *before* any GROQ projection. They drift from real data:
- Arrays include `_key` that projections often omit
- Strings are `string | undefined` (optional), but GROQ returns `string | null`
- Referenced assets are unresolved (no `url` field until you use `asset->`)

## Category 2 — Query result types (use these)
`PAGE_QUERY_RESULT`, `SITE_SETTINGS_QUERY_RESULT`, etc.
These reflect the exact shape of what your query actually returns.

## Rules

**❌ BAD — deriving props from schema document types:**
```typescript
import type { SiteSettings } from "sanity.types";
type NavigationProps = NonNullable<SiteSettings["navigation"]>;
// links items have _key and label?: string — but the query omits _key and returns label: string | null
```

**✅ GOOD — deriving props from query result types:**
```typescript
import type { SITE_SETTINGS_QUERY_RESULT } from "sanity.types";
type NavigationProps = NonNullable<NonNullable<SITE_SETTINGS_QUERY_RESULT>["navigation"]>;
// links items match exactly what the query projects
```

**❌ BAD — hardcoding types that mirror Sanity shapes:**
```typescript
type FaqBlock = { _type: string; children?: { text: string }[] };
type FaqItem  = { question?: string; answer?: FaqBlock[] };
type FaqMod   = { _type: "faq"; items?: FaqItem[] };
```

**✅ GOOD — extracting from the query result union:**
```typescript
import type { PAGE_QUERY_RESULT } from "sanity.types";
type PageModule  = NonNullable<NonNullable<PAGE_QUERY_RESULT>["modules"]>[number];
type FaqModule   = Extract<PageModule, { _type: "faq" }>;
type FaqItem     = NonNullable<FaqModule["items"]>[number];
```

## Corollary: no `as unknown[]` casts

If you need `as unknown[]` or similar escape hatches to pass Sanity data into a function, the function's parameter type is wrong. Fix it to accept the query result type instead.

## When to run typegen

Run `pnpm typegen` after any change to:
- Sanity schema files (`src/sanity/schemas/**`)
- GROQ queries (`src/sanity/queries.ts`)

Never edit `sanity.types.ts` manually.
